                {
                    "title": "<span style=\"font-size:26px;\">Key points</span>",
                    "content": "<ul class=\"key-points\">\n\t<li>Access to cash labor income was more limited for women (61%) than for men (70%) in developing regions, and even more limited for both women (57%) and men (64%) in sub-Saharan Africa.</li>\n\t<li>Access to cash labor income for women and men varied greatly across countries. The gender gap in cash-only labor income was higher than 10 percentage points in almost half (19) of countries with data.</li>\n</ul>\n",
                    "contentActions": [
                        []
                    ],
                    "creaDate": 1606788097941,
                    "pubDate": 1606788097941,
                    "status": "PUBLISHED",
                    "media": {
